    body:
      'Iter 146. Direct fix-forward on iter 145\'s regression — iter 145 bumped /api/price/latest/v1 from 5s to 10s and the sanity probe still timed out at 10000ms on Vercel while the VPS direct probe returned 200 in 0.24s × 3 samples at the same instant. The diagnosis from iter 145 verify was already correct: this is a Vercel-egress-specific stall on Taostats /price/latest, not a global Taostats outage and not a magnitude problem (bumping to 15s or 20s would buy the same regression on a wallet that gets unlucky with the rate-limit bucket). The right fix is to stop calling Taostats /price/latest on the hot path entirely. Iter 146 ships a server-side TAO price cache at module scope in lib/taostats.js with two thresholds: 60s fresh window (during which getTaoPrice() returns the cached value without any Taostats call), and a 5-minute stale-while-error window (during which a failed refetch falls back to the last-known price with a console.warn naming the age in seconds rather than throwing). Cache lives in module scope — survives warm-instance reuse on Vercel (typical lambda keepalive 5-10min, so a multi-wallet sweep that triggered the iter 145 regression now hits cache on wallet 2-7 instead of paying the egress tax 7 times), resets cleanly on cold starts so there\'s no cross-deploy poisoning vector. 60s freshness is conservative for an asset that moves <1% intraday — the worst-case user-visible drift is sub-cent on portfolio totals, which is well below the rounding visible in §2 PnL displays. Stale-while-error 5min ceiling tuned so a long outage like 2026-06-15 (4.5h) can NEVER masquerade as fresh data; at 5min the cache yields and the report fails loudly. Trade-off: if the very first request after a cold start hits a Vercel-egress stall, the cache has no fallback and the report still fails — but that\'s strictly no-worse-than the iter 145 status quo. Every subsequent request within the warm window is now resilient. This is the right shape regardless of root cause (geo-routing, per-IP-range throttle, post-outage degraded path, all three — none of those matter when we\'re not hitting the endpoint). Test-only exports _resetTaoPriceCache + _getTaoPriceCacheState added so smoke can assert cache hit/miss/stale-fallback behavior without reaching into module internals. Pre-commit smoke 11/11 PASS on isolated cases: cold cache fetches + caches the value, second call within 60s returns cached value without re-fetching (asserted by mocked taoGet call counter at 0), stale read past 60s but within 5min triggers refetch on success, refetch error within 5min serves stale value, refetch error past 5min throws, reset accessor clears state, getter accessor returns current state shape. Non-regressive: getTaoPrice signature unchanged, all 5+ callsites (paid PnL path, free-PnL preview, §0 verdict fanout, drawdown calc with price denomination, report-email USD conversion) get the same Number-typed return value, error case still throws on hard failure with no stale fallback available. Non-blocking on retroactive iter 142 verify: with iter 146 the retroactive verify sweep should run end-to-end if rate-limit-spaced ≥13s — first wallet primes the cache, wallets 2-7 hit cache instead of /price/latest. KB layer-stack unchanged (FIFTEEN — caching infra is reliability, not a new verdict axis). KB→§0 bridges unchanged (EIGHT). Iter 147 candidates: (a) FINISH the retroactive iter 142 verify on all 7 pinned coldkeys (now actually unblocked by iter 146 — rate-limit-spaced sweep should land cleanly), (b) extend the cache to /api/account/latest/v1 with a tighter 15s TTL since latest balance moves on every block (~12s) so 15s is the natural denomination, (c) "Taostats degraded" §0 banner now wired to the cache miss signal — if getTaoPrice returns stale value, the banner fires with the age, giving a much cleaner upstream signal than the iter 145 timeout-detection path, (d) per-section timeout budget tracking diagnostic panel. PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~19 days).',
