    tag: 'ai',
    title: 'PnL formula split — app now computes both the Drive-sheet accumulation formula (Σsell + current − Σbuy) and the harvest formula (current − (lifetimeIn − lifetimeOut)) alongside the existing window-scoped headline, classifies each wallet as accumulation/harvest from its transfer + delegation-event pattern, and surfaces the divergence as a 9th deterministic verdict row in §0 so the report names which sheet number to trust when the two formulas disagree',
    body:
      'Iter 142. Top-of-stack priority A from Jai\'s 2026-06-15 redirect — Drive-sheet PnL parity. Jai\'s Bittensor portfolio tracker (Drive id 10Nl8u…) uses two transfer-based formulas: accumulation wallets (Subnets / Mantat / Mum_subnets / Mum_mantat) read `net_pnl = Σsell + current − Σbuy`, harvest wallets (Root / Mum_root / Mum_smf) read `earnings = current − (transferIn − transferOut)`. Both reduce algebraically to `current + transferOut − transferIn` — the sheet never subtracts a window starting balance, it treats lifetime net funding as the cost basis. The app\'s existing headline `profitTao` reads `current + windowOut − windowIn − starting` which agrees with the sheet when the wallet is fresh-funded inside the window (starting≈0) but UNDER-COUNTS PnL on multi-year wallets where pre-window starting balance has already absorbed years of yield. Iter 142 ships the sheet\'s lifetime-transfer formula on the side so the divergence is visible without regressing the headline. Three changes: (1) lib/report.js buildReport — after the existing allTaxRows assembly (which already covers the previous + current FY for iter 137 multi-window analysis), tally lifetimeTransferInTao + lifetimeTransferOutTao across all rows, detect delegation_buy/delegation_sell events as the strongest accumulation signal, and compute walletTypeHeuristic = "accumulation" | "harvest" | "unknown" from (a) delegation event presence, (b) zero-transfer + positive daily-income (canonical harvest), or (c) bidirectional transfer count. Then derive sheetParityProfitTao = currentPortfolioTao − (lifetimeIn − lifetimeOut), formulaDivergenceTao = |profitTao − sheetParityProfitTao|, and a four-state parity verdict: matched (Δ < 0.05τ), harvest_preferred (heuristic = harvest, Δ ≥ threshold), accumulation_preferred (heuristic = accumulation, Δ ≥ threshold), divergent_unclassified (Δ ≥ threshold but classifier can\'t pick). All attached to gt.pnlFormulaParity with full reason strings naming both numbers. (2) lib/ai-insights.js buildVerdictFallback — 9th deterministic row between priceMomentum (iter 140, 8th) and emissionAlignment (iter 128/129, 10th) gated on gt.pnlFormulaParity.available + verdict. So §0 carries the formula-parity read through Pollinations outages alongside the durability + momentum + concentration + drawdown + staking-flow + emission-alignment trees. (3) lib/changelog-entries.js — this entry. Worked example: Jai\'s Root coldkey reads ~22.918τ current with funding events totalling ~22.7τ transfer_in years ago. The sheet\'s harvest formula yields 22.918 − (22.7 − 0) = +0.218τ (matches Jai\'s sheet truth row for Root). The app\'s window formula reads 22.918 + windowOut − windowIn − startingBalance where startingBalance is the trailing-FY snapshot value, which already absorbs all pre-window yield, so the window formula reports only the WITHIN-WINDOW yield — that\'s why headline historically diverged from the sheet on harvest wallets. The new parity verdict names this explicitly: "harvest_preferred — sheet earnings = current − (lifetimeIn − lifetimeOut) = 0.218τ; app\'s window formula yields X τ, diverging by Y τ (likely pre-window yield absorbed by starting-balance subtraction)". This iter is non-regressive: headline profitTao + pnlDecomposition + drawdown + staking-flow + price-momentum trees all unchanged. Iter 143 candidates: (a) once Jai validates the classifier on each of his 7 pinned wallets, promote sheetParityProfitTao to the headline (gated by walletTypeHeuristic), (b) extend the tax-row fetch backwards (FY23-24, FY22-23) for wallets where the 2-FY lifetime tally misses funding events (Bittensor mainnet only goes back to Mar 2021 and most subnet activity is 2024+, so this is bounded), (c) surface the parity verdict as a chip in the §2 PnL UI block beside the existing change pills. KB layer-stack climbs FOURTEEN → FIFTEEN with the formula-parity classifier (new axis: which sheet formula matches this wallet\'s economic shape). KB→§0 bridges climb SEVEN → EIGHT (added pnlFormulaParity 142). Smoke-tested locally: harvest pattern (zero transfers + daily income) → walletTypeHeuristic harvest, harvest_preferred verdict fires when Δ ≥ 0.05τ. Accumulation pattern (delegation events present) → accumulation_preferred. Identical formulas (starting=0) → matched. Truly empty wallet → pnlFormulaParity unavailable. Defensive against null gt and null currentPortfolioTao. Non-blocking: paid PnL flow + free-PnL preview branch + draft PR #1 still held pending Jai\'s 1/2/3 signoff.',
