    body:
      'Iter 117. Priority 2 (AI KB deepening) slice — another non-blocking addition while the free-PnL semantics-shift draft PR (#1) is still held pending Jai\'s 1/2/3 signoff. The user prompt already ships pnlGroundTruth.profitTao AND pnlGroundTruth.dailyIncomeTao (staking income over the window), but the KB had no framework for reading them as two components of one decomposition. Common failure mode: model anchors expectations on price-driven PnL (unrepeatable windfall) or dismisses a window where yield is structurally fine and only price is the headwind. New PNL_DECOMPOSITION block in lib/bittensor-kb.js codifies nine read-rules: (a) total PnL ≈ staking income + price contribution, read as a pair; (b) staking_income / total_pnl ≈ 1.0 → price flat, anchor on staking line not headline; (c) staking_income > total_pnl → price headwind, strategy structurally working even if optics bad, avoid "underperforming" framing; (d) total_pnl >> staking_income (3-5×) → price tailwind dominated, don\'t extrapolate; (e) window annualisation × (365 / window_days), compare to weighted APY — if implied annual >> weighted APY by a wide margin flag as front-loaded; (f) 24h vs daily-avg sanity check — 24h ≈ avg = steady, > 3× avg = fresh catalyst, ≈ 0 = stalled momentum; (g) negative PnL window + positive weighted APY → price-driven drawdown, target concentration/category mix not validator switching; (h) positive PnL window + very low weighted APY (< 5%) → return is almost entirely price momentum, name it so structural earn-rate weakness is visible. Appended into KB_TEXT after CATEGORY_HEURISTICS so the model sees the decomposition framework last, when it\'s about to write the actual narrative. Inference cost on Pollinations is $0; ~140 extra prompt tokens. Non-blocking: deterministic sections, paid PnL flow, free-PnL preview branch and draft PR #1 all untouched.',
